list.abstract: 《飞屋环游记》（Up）是一部由彼特·道格特、鲍勃·彼德森执导，彼特·道格特、鲍勃·彼德森、汤姆·麦卡锡担任编剧，爱德华·阿斯纳、克里斯托弗·普卢默、乔丹·长井等担任主要配音的喜剧冒险动画片，于2009年5月29日在美国上映，2009年8月4日在中国大陆上映。 该片主要讲述了一个老人曾经与老伴约定去一座坐落在遥远南美洲的瀑布旅行，却因为生活奔波一直未能成行，直到政府要强拆自己的老屋时才决定带着屋子一起飞向瀑布，路上与结识的小胖子罗素一起冒险的经历的故事。 2010年，该片获得第82届奥斯卡金像奖最佳动画长片、最佳影片提名奖。根据box office mojo官网显示，截至2009年12月该片累计全球票房7.35亿美元。

UP，英文单词，副词、介词、形容词、动词、名词，作副词时意为“向上；上涨；靠近（某人）；朝……的方向；到（重要地方）；向（国家北部的地方）；成碎片；彻底地；（以便）聚拢；（以便）完结；已结束；起床；（非正式）（不好的事情）发生；公开展示地；（航行）逆风地”，作介词时意为“向（较高位置）；沿着；在……之上；向……的较高处；到（向往之处）”，作形容词时意为“向上的；涨的；正在修正的；（骑师）骑着马的；（非正式）高兴的；完成的；起床的”，作动词时意为“突然做（意想不到的事）；提高……的价格（或数量）；举起”，作名词时意为“上升；繁荣；（非正式）走运”。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Britain is setting <highlight>up</highlight> a data ethics center.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国正在建立一个数据伦理中心。

examination_example.sentence: Each book opens <highlight>up</highlight> new avenues of knowledge to explore.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每本书都开辟了新的知识探索途径。

examination_example.sentence: For factory owners, it all adds <highlight>up</highlight> to stiff competition for workers – and upward pressure on wages.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对于工厂主来说，这一切加起来就导致了工人之间激烈的竞争和不断上涨的工资压力。

sense_info_list.zh: 提高; 上升; 加大

examination_example.sentence: Those rates had spiked <highlight>up</highlight> to 13.3 per cent and 13.7 per cent.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这两个比率分别飙升至13.3%和13.7%。

examination_example.sentence: Transient investors, who demand high quarterly profits from companies, can hinder a firm's efforts to invest in long-term research or to build <highlight>up</highlight> customer loyalty.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 要求从公司获得高额回报的短期投资者，会阻碍公司在长期研究和建立客户忠诚度的努力。

examination_example.sentence: Yet as distrust has risen toward all media, people may be starting to beef <highlight>up</highlight> their media literacy skills.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，随着对所有媒体的不信任上升，人们可能开始加强他们的媒体素养技能。

examination_example.sentence: In other words, they all share a view that the international tax system has failed to keep <highlight>up</highlight> with the current economy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 换句话说，他们都认为国际税收体系跟不上当前的经济。

examination_example.sentence: Students without experience can catch <highlight>up</highlight> after a few introductory courses.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 没有经验的学生可以在几门入门课程后赶上来。

examination_example.sentence: Graduates from elite universities tend to catch <highlight>up</highlight> quickly with experienced employees.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 精英大学的毕业生往往会很快赶上有经验的员工。

examination_example.sentence: Constant health scares just end <highlight>up</highlight> with one listening.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 持续的健康恐慌只会以一个人倾听而告终。

examination_example.sentence: Even when you win, you end <highlight>up</highlight> no better off.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 即使你赢了，你最终的境况也不会好起来。

examination_example.sentence: But too often we take this process too far and end <highlight>up</highlight> suppressing emotions, especially negative ones.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但我们往往把这个过程走得太远，最终压制了情绪，尤其是负面的情绪。

examination_example.sentence: One company in the UK, Phrasee, claims their software can outperform humans by <highlight>up</highlight> to 10 percent when it comes to email open rates.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国的一家公司Phrasee声称他们的软件在电子邮件打开率方面可以比人类高出10%。

examination_example.sentence: Runners range from four years old to grandparents; their times range from Andrew Baddeley's world record 13 minutes 48 seconds <highlight>up</highlight> to an hour.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 跑步者从四岁到祖父母辈都有，他们的用时区间从安德鲁·巴德利创造的世界记录13分钟48秒到一个小时不等。

examination_example.sentence: Journalists are known to have hacked the phones of <highlight>up</highlight> to 5, 500 people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 据了解，记者已经窃听了多达5500人的电话。

examination_example.sentence: We're also giving our customers better channels versus picking <highlight>up</highlight> the phone to accomplish something beyond human scale.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与拿起手机完成超出人力范围的任务相比，我们还为客户提供了更好的渠道。

examination_example.sentence: The same elite women scoop <highlight>up</highlight> multiple seats on a variety of boards.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同一批精英女性在各种董事会上抢占了多个席位。

examination_example.sentence: But once we rip off the band-aid, tuck our smartphones in our pockets and look <highlight>up</highlight>, it doesn't hurt so bad.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是，一旦我们撕掉了创可贴，把智能手机塞进口袋，抬起头来，它就不会那么痛了。

examination_example.sentence: And guilt, by prompting us to think more deeply about our goodness, can encourage humans to make <highlight>up</highlight> for errors and fix relationships.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 内疚，通过促使我们更深入地思考我们的善良，可以鼓励人类弥补错误，修复关系。

examination_example.sentence: Some kids who are low in sympathy may make <highlight>up</highlight> for that shortfall by experiencing more guilt, which can rein in their nastier impulses.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些都不那么有同情心的孩子，可以通过感受更多的内疚来弥补这种缺失，这可以遏制他们恶意的冲动。

examination_example.sentence: Nor was there any evidence that those who self-enhanced the most were doing so to make <highlight>up</highlight> for profound insecurities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也没有任何证据表明那些自我提升程度最大的人这样做是为了弥补自身强烈的不安全感。

examination_example.sentence: A generation has grown <highlight>up</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一代人已经长大了。

examination_example.sentence: I still grew <highlight>up</highlight> in an upper middle-class home with parents who didn't have college degrees.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我仍然成长在一个中上阶层的家庭，父母没有大学文凭。

examination_example.sentence: As we grow <highlight>up</highlight>, we learn to control our emotions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着我们的成长，我们学会了控制自己的情绪。

examination_example.sentence: Some of the success of plant-based meat can be chalked <highlight>up</highlight> to shoppers wanting to signal their desire to protect the environment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 植物肉的成功在一定程度上可以归因于消费者想要表达他们保护环境的愿望。

examination_example.sentence: But, the wonderful thing about failure is that it's entirely <highlight>up</highlight> to us to decide how to look at it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但失败的美妙之处在于，如何看待失败完全取决于我们自己。

examination_example.sentence: My concern with leaving it <highlight>up</highlight> to the individual, however, is our limited sense of what needs to be achieved.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，我对由个人决定的担忧是，我们对需要实现的目标的认识有限。

examination_example.sentence: Businesses should engage in conversations with teams to review their privacy, and include in the discussion the marketers and advertisers responsible for sign-<highlight>ups</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 企业应该与团队进行对话，审查他们的隐私，并让负责注册的营销人员和广告商参与讨论。

examination_example.sentence: Think about the times you felt tricked by a membership that had a seamless sign-<highlight>up</highlight> process but was later difficult to cancel.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 想想你被一个拥有无缝注册过程但后来很难取消的会员资格所欺骗的时候。

examination_example.sentence: Reding invited corporations to sign <highlight>up</highlight> for gender balance goals of 40 per cent female board membership.
examination_example.sentence_trans: Reding邀请企业签署性别平衡目标，即董事会女性成员比例达到40%。

examination_example.sentence: When taken <highlight>up</highlight> by broadcasters and the lay press, this kind of nonsense generates both health scares and short-lived dietary enthusiasms.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当被广播公司和外行媒体报道时，这些无稽之谈就会就会引发健康恐慌和短暂的饮食热潮。

examination_example.sentence: But her appeal was considered a failure: only 24 companies took it <highlight>up</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是她的呼吁被认为是失败的: 只有24家公司接受了。

examination_example.sentence: The web's full of articles offering tips on making time to read: "Give <highlight>up</highlight> TV" or "Carry a book with you at all times."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 网上充斥着各种教你如何腾出时间来阅读的攻略：诸如“放弃看电视”或者“随时带本书在身边”。

examination_example.sentence: Second, paper checks have the advantage that they provide receipts, something that many consumers are unwilling to give <highlight>up</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 纸质支票的优势在于它能提供收据，这是许多消费者不愿意放弃的东西。

examination_example.sentence: Cover <highlight>up</highlight> their depressions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 掩盖他们的沮丧。

examination_example.sentence: My collection of "Smiling Victorians" makes <highlight>up</highlight> only a tiny percentage of the vast catalogue of photographic portraiture created between 1840 and 1900.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我收藏的“微笑的维多利亚人”只占了1840年到1900年创作的大量肖像摄影作品的一小部分。

examination_example.sentence: How do the people you respect and look <highlight>up</highlight> to present themselves?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你尊敬和敬仰的人是如何表现自己的？

examination_example.sentence: to give voters more public figures to look <highlight>up</highlight> to
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了让选民有更多的公众人物去尊敬

examination_example.sentence: How do you decide whether it's worth speaking <highlight>up</highlight>?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你如何决定它是否值得完全说出来?

examination_example.sentence: Since technology has such an insatiable appetite for eating <highlight>up</highlight> human jobs, this phenomenon will continue to restructure our economy in ways we cannot immediately foresee.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 由于技术如此贪婪地吞噬着人类的工作， 所以这一现象将会以我们当前难以预料的方式重构我们的经济。

examination_example.sentence: Taking <highlight>up</highlight> odd jobs.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 打零工。

examination_example.sentence: A lot of students take <highlight>up</highlight> law as their profession.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 许多学生将法律作为职业。

examination_example.sentence: They put <highlight>up</highlight> with the experiment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们忍受了这个实验。

examination_example.sentence: Journalists'made-<highlight>up</highlight> stories.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 记者编造的故事。

examination_example.sentence: In Europe, some are <highlight>up</highlight> in arms over a proposal to drop a specific funding category for social-science research.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在欧洲，一些人强烈反对取消社会科学研究特定资助类别的提议。

examination_example.sentence: The number of adults doing weekly sport did rise, by nearly 2 million in the run-<highlight>up</highlight> to 2012— but the general population was growing faster.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每周锻炼身体的成年人数量的确在2012年前增加了将近两百万，但总人口增长速度更快。

examination_example.sentence: Doubtless a piece of boiled beef can always be served <highlight>up</highlight> on Sunday alongside some steamed vegetables, without the Yorkshire pudding and no wine.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 毫无疑问，一块水煮牛肉总是可以在周日和一些蒸蔬菜一起上桌，不吃约克郡布丁也不喝葡萄酒。

examination_example.sentence: We humans count on forests to soak <highlight>up</highlight> a good share of the carbon dioxide we produce.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们人类指望森林吸收我们产生的大量二氧化碳。

examination_example.sentence: His biographies of James Watt, Richard Arkwright and Josiah Wedgwood were held <highlight>up</highlight> as beacons to guide the working man through his difficult life.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他写的关于詹姆斯·瓦特、理查德·阿克赖特和约西亚·韦奇伍德的传记被奉为是指引工人们度过艰难生活的灯塔。

examination_example.sentence: Look <highlight>up</highlight> Homo sapiens in the "Red List" of threatened species of the International Union for the Conversation of Nature (IUCN)
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在国际自然保护联盟(IUCN)的濒危物种“红色名单”中查阅智人。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Up</highlight> until a few decades ago, our visions of the future were largely — though by no means uniformly — glowingly positive.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 直至几十年前，我们对未来的展望很大程度上——尽管绝非一致——都是乐观积极的。

examination_example.sentence: While these measures would be welcome in the short term, we must face <highlight>up</highlight> to the fact.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 虽然这些措施短期内会受到欢迎，但我们一定要正视现实。

examination_example.sentence: The move to renewables is picking <highlight>up</highlight> momentum around the world.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 全球范围内，可再生能源的发展势头正在加快。
